<h3 id=3D"DatastaxAstraQuickStartGuideforlocaldevelopment-Step4:Update/Crea=
teConfigurationFiles"><strong>Step 4: Update/Create Configuration Files</st=
rong></h3>
<p>Create two configuration files in your project directory:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>mesh-datastore.conf place it in env/local/mesh-datastore.conf</co=
de></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh-datastore.conf</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: RDark" data-theme=3D"RDark"># This configuratio=
n is to connect to Datastax Astra
# For local testing you will need to request this conf file and the zip fil=
e as described
# here: https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/VmywVw
include file("../../../../secrets/local/mesh-datastore-secrets.conf")

datastax-java-driver {
  basic {
    # change this to match the target keyspace for your component
=09# Probably replace the dashes in the names with underscores.
    session-keyspace =3D inf_bnkng_resrcitm_logclitcmpnt_refdatastr_v1
    cloud {
=09  # For local testing this is going to be the location of the zip file. =
Don't unzip it.
      secure-connect-bundle =3D "../../../../secrets/local/secure-connect-a=
008e0-default.zip"
    }
  }
} </pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><code>mesh-datastore-secrets.conf place it in /secrets/local folder)</c=
ode></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh-datastore-secrets.conf</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: RDark" data-theme=3D"RDark">datastax-java-dri=
ver {
  advanced {
    auth-provider {
      class =3D PlainTextAuthProvider
      # change below to match the appropriate credentials
      username =3D "user_name(Obtained from service desk)"
      password =3D "password(Obtained from service desk)"
    }
  }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
