<h1 id=3D"IntroductiontoDatastores-WhatisaMeshDatastore?"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(51,51,153);"><strong>What is a Mesh Datastore?</strong></span></h1=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The Mesh Datastore component lever=
ages the Datastax Astra that are compliant with the Cassandra API (</span><=
a href=3D"https://docs.datastax.com/en/astra-serverless/docs/index.html" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.datastax.com/en/astra-s=
erverless/docs/index.html</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">)</span>=
</p>
<h2 id=3D"IntroductiontoDatastores-BeforeyouStart:"><span style=3D"color: r=
gb(0,0,128);"><strong>Before you Start:&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Your project team, including your=
 Solutions Architect, have read and understood the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://=
confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MD/Datastax+Astra+-+Solution+Scope" r=
el=3D"nofollow">criteria </a>for this MVP MESH datastore service</span></li=
>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">TEP has been approved, and your p=
</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">roject name has been set-up in=
 the Westpac Mesh Service desk<span>.</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>Bitbucket Repository has be=
en created as per the process mentioned in the confluence page:&nbsp;<a hre=
f=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+Create+a+Bit=
bucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">How to Create a Bitbucket Repository</a=
>.</span></span></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Deve=
loper+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer tools</a><span>&nbsp;</span>ar=
e installed on your local machine.</li>
<li>Make sure you read&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/Designing+My+First+Dat=
a+Store+-+Cassandra">Designing My First Data Store - Cassandra</a>&nbsp;bef=
ore writing any CQL.</li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-=
information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Before your new datastore can be deployed or used for the first time, yo=
u need to ensure that a DB service (Data service) has been created to host =
it.</p>
<p>Each DB service is dedicated to a particular Mesh domain (for example "D=
igital", or "Customer Interactions &amp; Insights") and the Data service (u=
sually 'default').</p>
<p>To create a service, raise a request with the Mesh/Westpac Mesh Support =
Desk.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279840">Step 1: Creating a datastore in the Westpac Mesh=
</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"379e9fb2-70fd-4e89-b753-7ef0abdc=
485c-1203279840">
<h2 id=3D"Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.1:Initialisethedat=
astorerepository"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);"><style type=3D"tex=
t/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1773923237331 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1773923237331 ul {margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1773923237331 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style>
