<li><a href=3D"#Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Example">Example</=
a></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li><a href=3D"#Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.3:Consumptio=
nGrantsforAPIs">Step 1.3: Consumption Grants for APIs</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.4:Applythech=
angestothedatastore,build&amp;deploy!">Step 1.4: Apply the changes to the d=
atastore, build &amp; deploy!</a></li>
</ul>
</div><br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">S</span><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">tep 1.1: Initialise the datastore repository</s=
pan></h2>
<p>Datastore component, like any other Mesh component, is a construct which=
 uses a repository to store its information.</p>
<p>Before we can create a datastore, we need to have a valid name for it. O=
ur datastore name has to conform to the naming standards described here:&nb=
sp;<a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1203279226">Datastore/ Table =
Naming Standards</a></p>
<p>When we have decided upon a name, we have to then get it approved by the=
 governance team.</p>
<p>After the approval, dispatch a request on Service Desk&nbsp;with the Wes=
tpac Mesh Gatekeeper team, who will then initialise the repository for us.<=
/p>
<p>An example datastore repository can be found <a href=3D"https://bitbucke=
t.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt=
-refdatastr-v1-datastore/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">h=
ere</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"915314b3-d41d-434c-b3d=
e-50589fa4b460">As it is with all components, Mesh Datastore holds its basi=
c properties in its </span><em><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker=
" data-ref=3D"915314b3-d41d-434c-b3de-50589fa4b460">component.yaml</span></=
strong></em><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"915314b3-d41d=
-434c-b3de-50589fa4b460"> file. There is a good chance this file wouldn't n=
eed to be changed once Gatekeeper has created it, since they already set th=
e right values for the properties.</span></p>
