<p></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">Important elements of a Datastore's co=
mponent.yaml</p><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info co=
nfluence-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><em> componentType: datastore&nbsp;// Describes that this component is a=
 Datastore</em><br><em>contractType: cassandra&nbsp;// Describes the type o=
f datastore, for now this is limited to Cassandra only</em><br><em>dataServ=
ice: default&nbsp;// Describes the dataService name, for most cases this wi=
ll be default unless a datastore has special service requirements</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>More information on Datastore Component Type:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"/dis=
play/WDPIPAAS/Datastore+Component+Type">Datastore Component Type</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.2:CreatetheCQLfile=
stoinitialisethedatastore"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">Step 1.2:=
 Create the CQL files to initialise the datastore</span></h2>
<p>After the repository has been created in Step 1.1, we can now focus on c=
reating a schema for our datastore!</p>
<p>The schema and tables are also to be created in accordance with the stan=
dards described here:&nbsp;<a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D12032=
79226">Datastore/ Table Naming Standards</a></p>
<p>The datastore schema information is contained in CQL files inside the&nb=
sp;<em><strong>changesets&nbsp;</strong></em>directory in the repository as=
 seen here:</p>
