 from a single API call, comprising a business transaction. This MUST be pr=
opagated
organisation_id: The organisation the caller is operating in. This MUST be =
propagated
originating_system_id: Alfabet Id of calling application e.g. A00304. This =
MUST be propagated
consumer_type: The originating consumption channel invoking the API (eg. Pa=
rtner, Staff, Customer). This MUST be propagated
user_id: The unique identifier for the user invoking the API (eg. Staff sal=
ary number, Customer CIS/GCIS key, Partner CIS/GCIS key or other identifier=
). This MUST be propagated
user_id_scheme: The scheme (type) applicable for the user identifier of the=
 consumer invoking the API. This MUST be propagated
originating_bsb: Identifies the BSB from which this request originated. The=
 format should be XXY-ZZZ. The first two digits (XX) specify the bank or fi=
nancial institution. The third digit (Y) tells which state the branch is lo=
cated in. The last three digits (ZZZ) specify the address of the branch. Th=
is MUST be propagated
originating_device_id: Identifies the device from which this request origin=
ated.  The device could be a staff computer, ATM, internal server, mobile d=
evice. This MUST be propagated
on_behalf_of_id: The unique identifier for the party on whose behalf the us=
er identified by x-userId is acting. (eg. Customer internal identifier such=
 as CIS/GCIS key). This MUST be propagated
on_behalf_of_id_scheme: The scheme (type) applicable for the party on whose=
 behalf the user identified by x-userId is acting. This MUST be propagated
last_updated_date_time: Date-time the record last updated. This will be inj=
ected by the framework
*/

CREATE TYPE mesh_header (
   message_id text,
   app_correlation_id text,
   organisation_id text,
   originating_system_id text,
   consumer_type text,
   user_id text,
   user_id_scheme text,
   originating_bsb text,
   originating_device_id text,
   on_behalf_of_id text,
   on_behalf_of_id_scheme text,
   last_updated_date_time timestamp
);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Every table is&nbsp;<strong>REQUIR=
ED&nbsp;</strong>to include a <em><strong>mesh_header&nbsp;</strong></em>co=
lumn, which is a user defined type (UDT), this is elaborated below:</span><=
/p>
