ning"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-=
information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Schema changes must&nbsp;<strong>not</strong> be destructive. For exampl=
e DROP TABLE followed by CREATE TABLE raises an&nbsp;<strong>unacceptable r=
isk of data loss</strong>.</p>
<p>If a schema needs to be reset in development or early testing there is a=
 separate feature to perform this action on request. This will completely r=
eset your datastore (keyspace) and re-run all of your current cql.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.3:ConsumptionGrant=
sforAPIs"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">Step 1.3: Consumption Gran=
ts for APIs</span></h2>
<p>To consume datastores, APIs need to be given either reader/writer access=
 to the datastore. This is done by:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>The API developer requesting consumption of the datastore for reading o=
r for writing; and</li>
<li>The datastore owner(s) approving the consumption of the datastore.</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that the sample API (v2) also leverages operation-level access cont=
rol, this is&nbsp;<em>not</em> required for using datastores and the existi=
ng pattern of a read API / and a 'maint' API is also fully supported.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Step1:CreatingadatastoreintheWestpacMesh-Step1.4:Applythechangest=
othedatastore,build&amp;deploy!"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">Ste=
p 1.4: Apply the changes to the datastore, build &amp; deploy!</span></h2>
<p>After the CQL files have been finalised, the changes maybe pushed to the=
 datastore repository's feature branch.</p>
<p>Merge the changes to <em>master</em>, so that the datastore build may be=
 executed.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
Every datastore will have a build pipeline associated with it, for example =
the wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-refdatastr-v2-datastore has <a href=
=3D"https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/WDPBUILDDS-ID13UB" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">this build pipeline</a>.
</div>
</div>
<p>Once the build completes it will trigger the deployment pipeline which w=
ill apply the change-sets to the datastore in the Astra service, for an exa=
mple deployment see builds here: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:/=
/bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/label/component_name%3Dinf-bnkng-resr=
citm-logclitcmpnt-refdatastr-v2" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bamboo-wdp.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/browse/label/component_name%3Dinf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-=
refdatastr-v2</a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279841">Step 2: Consuming the Datastore</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"379e9fb2-70fd-4e89-b753-7ef0abdc=
485c-1203279841">
<p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1773923237864 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1773923237864 ul {margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1773923237864 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1773923237864">
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">
<li><a href=3D"#Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-Step2.1:InitialisetheAPIreposit=
ory,andadddependencies.yaml">Step 2.1: Initialise the API repository, and a=
dd dependencies.yaml</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-Step2.2:AddingAPIfunctionality"=
>Step 2.2: Adding API functionality</a>
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">
<li><a href=3D"#Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-QueryAPIs(Readers)">Query APIs =
(Readers)</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-MaintenanceAPIs(Writers)">Maint=
enance APIs (Writers)</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-UseMeshHeaderHelperlibrarytopop=
ulateMeshHeaderforinsert/updates">Use Mesh Header Helper library to populat=
e Mesh Header for insert/updates</a></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div><br>
 The datastore, once created and deployed as described in the previous sect=
ion, may then be used to store information. APIs would then need to be deve=
loped which have access to perform CRUD operation on this datastore. The AP=
I READMEs below describe in detail the APIs and their main constructs. The =
source code provides guidance to developers on how to develop APIs to consu=
me datastores effectively.=20
<p></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-=
information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Cassandra is a NoSQL database, and does not work in the same way as an R=
DBMS:</p>
<ul>
<li>you must use a primary key for queries, table scans or 'allow filtering=
' will probably result in a failed project</li>
<li>there are no multi-table joins</li>
<li>secondary indexes don't help in most cases</li>
<li>you will often need to implement inserts or updates to multiple tables,=
 because your data must be denormalised to support efficient queries</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"Step2:ConsumingtheDatastore-Step2.1:InitialisetheAPIrepository,an=
dadddependencies.yaml"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">Step 2.1: Ini=
tialise the API repository, and add dependencies.yaml</span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">In your API's repository, add the <st=
rong>datastore name</strong> and the&nbsp;<strong>role</strong> in the <em>=
<strong>dependencies.yaml</strong></em> as shown below. The following examp=
le shows how requiring access from&nbsp;<em><strong>inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logc=
litcmpnt-refdatastr-v1</strong></em> with role <em><strong>writer</strong><=
/em></span></p>
