<div class=3D"include4confluence-panel-content-container ">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-code-content">
<pre style=3D"font-size: 12px;"># Mesh Platform Cassandra Helper Library (m=
esh-platform-cassandra)

## Preface

This library is specifically to assist the developers in the population of =
the Mesh Header in requests as described
here:

`https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/=
templates/000_mesh_header_cassandra.cql`

MeshHeader is mapped to a User Defined Type (UDT) in the Cassandra database=
. This UDT should exist for all datastores
created on the Mesh Platform. This UDT is referenced in tables as `mesh_hea=
der` with type
`frozen&lt;header&gt;` as illustrated here:
https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-technolmgt-=
pltf-integ-ref-cassandra-v1-datastore/browse/changesets/001_initial.cql

This library uses the `mesh-platfomr-context` library embedded in `ubi-tomc=
at10` containers to populate the API request headers
without developer intervention. These headers compose the `header` column w=
hich is then to be persisted in the table
with datastore table insertion/update.

The library populates the `last_updated_date_time` field with the current i=
nstant everytime a new MeshHeader is
generated. It advised that an instance of MeshHeader is retrieved from the =
library on every call, and all subsequent
calls use the same header. This is demonstrated in the `inf-bnkng-resrcitm-=
logclitcmpnt-refdatastrmaint-v1` API

# Usage

- Include the `mesh-platform-cassandra` in your project:

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;au.com.westpac.mesh.commons&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;mesh-platform-cassandra&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;1.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```
## Bean-Mapped
- This has been demonstrated by the Datastore Maintenance API (Refer to: [A=
pplicationsServiceHelperImpl.java](https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/pro=
jects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-refdatastrmaint-v1-api/=
browse/src/main/java/au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitcmpnt/refdata=
strmaint/v1/api/impl/ApplicationsServiceHelperImpl.java))
### Inserting the MeshHeader
If your API/Listener is using the Datastax driver with entity mapping, you =
need to:
* Add the `MeshHeader` to the table's entity, along with relevant getter/se=
tter
```java
    @CqlName("mesh_header")
    private MeshHeader meshHeader;
```
* Use the table's DAO to save that entity into the datastore:
```java
// productDao is the DAO Mapper object, and product is the entity's instanc=
e with a populated MeshHeader field
 product.setMeshHeader(MeshHeaderUtils.getMeshHeader());
 productDao.save(product);
```
### Retrieving the MeshHeader from a table row
```java
// Use the DAO to retrieve the table row by providing the arguments
ApplicationDetails application =3D applicationDao.findApplicationDetailsByA=
pplicationId(applicationId);

// Print the MeshHeader
logger.info("Retrieved MeshHeader {}", application.getMeshHeader().getMessa=
geId());
```

## Parameterized Queries
### Inserting the MeshHeader
```java
// Define the INSERT QUERY
public static final String INSERT_CUSTOMER =3D "INSERT INTO application_id_=
by_customer_id (application_id, customer_id, last_updated_time, mesh_header=
) values (:ai, :ci, :lut, :h)";

// Get the CQL Session, with the prepare query
PreparedStatement prepared =3D ConnectionUtils.getCqlSession().prepare(INSE=
RT_CUSTOMER);

// Bind Variables to their placeholders in the query
BoundStatement bound =3D prepared.bind()
                               .setString("ai", applicationId)
                               .setString("ci", customerId)
                               .setInstant("lut", lastUpdatedTime)
                               .setUdtValue("h", MeshHeaderUtils.getMeshHea=
derUdtValue(ConnectionUtils.getMeshHeaderUdt()));
// Execute the query
boolean success =3D ConnectionUtils.getCqlSession().execute(bound).wasAppli=
ed();
```
### Retrieving the MeshHeader from a table row
```java
// Define SELECT query
public static final String SELECT_MESH_HEADER =3D "SELECT mesh_header FROM =
application_details_by_application_id WHERE application_id=3D:ai";

// Prepare the query
PreparedStatement ps =3D ConnectionUtils.getCqlSession().prepare(SELECT_MES=
H_HEADER);

// Bind Variables
BoundStatement boundStatement =3D ps.bind().setString("ai", applicationId);

// Execute Query
Row row =3D ConnectionUtils.getCqlSession().execute(boundStatement).one();

// Get the MeshHeader UdtValue
UdtValue udtValue =3D row.getUdtValue("mesh_header");

// Print the value
logger.info("Retrieved message_id: {}", udtValue.getString("message_id"));
```
### Exposed functions
- In your datastore consuming API, use the following functions to get the `=
MeshHeader` object.
    - `MeshHeaderUtils.getMeshHeader()` returns the `MeshHeader` object wit=
h all the fields populated.
    - `MeshHeaderUtils.getMeshHeaderUdtValue(UserDefinedType udt)` takes th=
e `mesh_header` UDT type as
      an input which is unique for every keyspace and returns a `UdtValue` =
object
      which maybe used by Datastax Cassandra Driver's PreparedStatement.
        -   `MeshHeaderUtils.getMeshHeaderUdtValue(MeshHeader meshHeader, U=
serDefinedType udt)` takes the `mesh_header`
            UDT type, and pre-populated `meshHeader` object as input return=
s a `UdtValue` object with values populated from
            the `MeshHeader` object. This `UdtValue` object can be used by =
Datastax Cassandra Driver's PreparedStatement.

# Further Information
### ConnectionUtils.getMeshHeaderUdt()
To insert a new instance of mesh_header UDT in a table, a UserDefinedType o=
bject representing the field needs to be
retrieved. The preferred method of doing this is calling the `ConnectionUti=
ls.getMeshHeaderUdt()` function:
```java
public static UserDefinedType getMeshHeaderUdt() {
        return ConnectionUtils.getCqlSession()
                              .getMetadata()
                              .getKeyspace(ConfigurationUtils.getKeySpaceNa=
me())
                              .flatMap(ks -&gt; ks.getUserDefinedType(MESH_=
HEADER))
                              .orElseThrow(() -&gt; new IllegalArgumentExce=
ption("Missing UDT definition for mesh_header"));
    }
```

- The `inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-refdatastrmaint-v1` API demonstrates=
 the usage for this library in
  `ApplicationsServiceHelperImpl` class
    - https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng=
-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-refdatastrmaint-v1-api/browse
- Headers: https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/WDPIPAAS/API+HTTP+=
Header+Parameters   =20

#### Versions
* `0.x.x`
  * Supports JDK11
  * groupId - `au.com.westpac.wdp.commons.mesh.platform`
  * artifactId - `lib-mesh-platform-cassandra`
  * Datastax Driver 4.11.0, groupId - `com.datastax.oss`
* `1.x.x`
  * Supports JDK21
  * groupId - `au.com.westpac.mesh.commons`
  * artifactId - `mesh-platform-cassandra`
  * Datastax Driver 4.18.1, groupId - `org.apache.cassandra`
  * Netty Common 4.1.115.Final, excluded netty-common from datastax driver =
dependency to resolve snyk issue</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279842">Step 3: Deploying Reader/Writer APIs</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"379e9fb2-70fd-4e89-b753-7ef0abdc=
485c-1203279842">
<p>After the APIs have been developed, a build may then be created, and dep=
loyed to the respective environment.</p>
<p>Each API has its own <strong>Build Pipeline</strong> like <a href=3D"htt=
ps://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/WDPBUILDAPI-ID12TZ-22" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">this example</a>. and there is also one <str=
ong>Deployment Pipeline</strong> for each environment, like <a href=3D"http=
s://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/WDPDEPLOYAPIDEV1-APIDEPLOYDEV1-354=
21" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">this one for DEV</a>.&nbsp;</p=
>
<h2 id=3D"Step3:DeployingReader/WriterAPIs-Step3.1:DebuggingInformationavai=
lableindeployments"><span style=3D"color: rgb(128,0,128);">Step 3.1: Debugg=
ing Information available in deployments</span></h2>
<p>The properties injected during the deployment of an API consuming a data=
store maybe inspected in the API's Deployment <strong>"Upsert Datastore"&nb=
sp;</strong>stage.</p>
<p>The upserted properties can be seen in Step 2.2 in the attached API's RE=
ADME.</p>
<p>These logs maybe used to ascertain the correct properties are being inje=
cted.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<h1 id=3D"DatastoresDeveloperDocumentation-ContactsforassistancewithWestpac=
MeshEngagementandServiceDeskTeams:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><s=
trong>Contacts for assistance with Westpac Mesh Engagement and Service Desk=
 Teams:</strong></span></h1>
<ul>
<li>Westpac Mesh Engagement:&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"mailto=
:WDPEngagement@westpac.com.au" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">WDPEngagement@westpac.com.au</a></li>
<li>Westpac Mesh Service Desk:&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"mail=
to:WDPSupport@westpac.com.au" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofol=
low">WDPSupport@westpac.com.au</a></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279843">MESH Datastore Criteria</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"87f6a554-92a2-42e5-8a50-933f9df4=
af55-1203279843">
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>Before using Mesh Datastore=
, ensure you meet these criteria: <a style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);" href=3D=
"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D15287=
42921" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Datastore Criteria (1) - Westpac Mesh - Westpa=
c Enterprise Confluence</a></strong></span></p>
<p>The Mesh Datastore component currently leverages Cassandra DB instances =
that are compliant with</p>
<ol>
<li>The Cassandra API with (very few) exceptions: <a href=3D"https://docs.d=
atastax.com/en/astra-db-serverless/cql/cassandra-guardrails.html" class=3D"=
external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.datastax.com/en/astra-db-serve=
rless/cql/cassandra-guardrails.html</a></li>
<li>Native Cassandra Offering from DataStax Astra. Read further on this pag=
e.</li>
</ol>
<p>The original offering leveraged Azure Cosmos DB using the Cassandra comp=
atibility feature. This is&nbsp;<em>mostly</em> compliant with OSS Cassandr=
a. See exceptions here:<span>&nbsp;</span><a class=3D"external-link" style=
=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/=
cosmos-db/cassandra/cassandra-support" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.micros=
oft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/cassandra/cassandra-support</a>), for more de=
tails on this offering, refer to the details here: <a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/PCSTEAM/Mesh+Datastore+**Phase1**+-+Azure+=
cosmos+db" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Datastore **Phase1** - Azure cosmos db - P=
ublic Cloud Services - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-=
information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>The Azure Cosmos DB service is closed for new projects. Public Cloud Ser=
vices intend to decommission the Azure VPC platform in future in order to f=
ocus on Azure ELZ.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>The Mesh Datastore feature, like a traditional database, supports persis=
tent data in production. Therefore, we expect that the schema is designed a=
nd reviewed before implementation. The Architecture community can assist wi=
th datastore schema design reviews.</p>
<p>Schema changes needed after the initial release of a datastore must be g=
overned by each project to protect against data loss in production (just as=
 for existing database service). For example, a change dropping tables or c=
olumns is dangerous and could result in <strong>data loss in production</st=
rong>.</p>
<p>The Mesh Datastore feature is<span>&nbsp;</span><em>not</em> a SQL RDBMS=
 and is not ACID-compliant. The schema design must take the features of Cas=
sandra into account. Designs for Oracle or SQL Server cannot be reused in a=
 Cassandra database without review and rework.</p>
<p>The Cassandra instances are hosted in Azure in single-region high-Availa=
bility zones with 99.9% uptime.</p>
<p>Project teams and solutions architects must consider the following crite=
ria before using this service:</p>
<ul>
<li>Caters for a workload up to 80TPS read and 15TPS write (simultaneous)</=
li>
<li>We expect a write to be under 1KB in size and read to be under 4KB in s=
ize</li>
<li>Disk space up to 50GB</li>
<li>One datastore per service</li>
<li>Project teams must complete SVP to confirm capacity required to support=
 the solution.</li>
<li>OPEX charged to the project, may increase if additional resources, disk=
 capacity are needed.</li>
<li>Westpac Mesh component costs can be found&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MD/MESH+On-boarding+Component+Pricing" rel=
=3D"nofollow">here.</a></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 60.=
5515%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 8.27907%;">
<col style=3D"width: 91.7209%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th colspan=3D"2" scope=3D"colgroup" class=3D"confluenceTh"><strong>Datasto=
re Backup &amp; Restore&nbsp;</strong></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Retention</strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Short term only - Currently 20 days, being uplifted to 32 days.</li>
<li>No long-term retention</li>
<li>Tenants are expected to be aware of the Westpac Group data management s=
tandard and the individual business application obligations around the shor=
t/long term retention.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Frequency</strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Periodic backups only - every hour (no point in time visibility)</li>
<li>RPO - 1 hour</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Testing</strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>DataStax backups are automated but restore requires manual intervention=
.</li>
<li>Tenants are expected to:=20
<ul>
<li>Perform backup and restore tests as per Westpac TCL standard applicable=
 to individual business applications.</li>
<li>Oblige to the operational runbooks and processes to perform the testing=
 and align to RPO.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Downtime</strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Restores are in-place and requires downtime of the entire database owne=
d by an application, restores can be performed at DB, datastore(keyspace) o=
r table level though.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<hr>
